# Rust
target/
# Typical guidance:
# Remove Cargo.lock from gitignore if creating an executable, leave it for libraries
# More information here https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/guide/cargo-toml-vs-cargo-lock.html
# Seems like many ignore this and commit Cargo.lock anyway to ensure consistent builds.
# Let's consider keeping it and not ignoring it.
# Ignoring it because it might help build the library for different environments.
Cargo.lock
